snippet.title: Amber Heard Did Not Keep Her Word To ACLU Yet
snippet.description:
Amber Heard said she would give the entire 7 million dollars that she received from the divorce settlement with Johnny Depp to Children's Hospital and the ACLU domestic violence unit, in equal shares, but the deal unraveled after Johnny said he would just give the money directly to both organizations. Johnny paid the first installment of $200k  $100k to Children's and $100k to the ACLU.
But now it seems neither organization got any money after that and the settlement deal still hasn't been signed.  However, an ACLU rep acknowledged that Amber made a $350k payment on August 19th, 2016. A source connected with Amber says she advanced the money, relying on Johnny paying her the settlement. 
Sources also said that although Amber made it a point to send Children's Hospital the money, she didnt get to proceed because she and Johnny began squabbling over the settlement deal.
Amber's lawyer, Pierce O'Donnell, says he's confident the settlement will be signed very soon.
